# Apana Swastha Kendra ERP — Complete Rebuild Plan

## Problem Statement

The current ERP system has a partially built Spring Boot backend and React frontend, but suffers from numerous issues that prevent it from working properly. After thorough analysis of all 140+ backend Java files, 16 frontend pages, and 9 reusable components, here is the full diagnosis and rebuild plan.

---

## Current State Analysis

### What Exists & Works (Partially)
- ✅ Spring Boot project structure with 14 packages
- ✅ JWT auth flow (login, bootstrap, refresh, logout)
- ✅ User entity with role hierarchy and scope filtering
- ✅ Permission catalog system (complex but functional)
- ✅ Geographic hierarchy entities (State, District, Block, Center)
- ✅ Basic OPD/IPD entities and service layer
- ✅ Pharmacy FIFO dispense logic
- ✅ Billing/Invoice with basic commission
- ✅ Wallet entity with credit/debit
- ✅ Notification entity
- ✅ React + Vite + Tailwind setup with routing

### Critical Issues Found

#### Backend Issues
| # | Issue | Severity |
|---|-------|----------|
| 1 | **Commission system broken** — Creates a single flat commission instead of hierarchical distribution (Associate 4% → Block 3% → District 2% → State 1% → Platform 0.5%) | 🔴 Critical |
| 2 | **No Family/Health Card system** — Patients registered directly, no family grouping, no card number generation (ASK-BH-PTN-003-00045 format) | 🔴 Critical |
| 3 | **UHID format wrong** — Currently `HOSP-2026-000001`, spec requires `ASK-{state}-{district}-{block}-{serial}` | 🔴 Critical |
| 4 | **Missing `CENTER_MANAGER` role in enum** — Code references it but the `Role.java` enum doesn't have it (only goes to `CENTER_STAFF`) | 🟡 Major |
| 5 | **No vendor management module** — Vendor catalog, ordering, and center inventory missing entirely | 🟡 Major |
| 6 | **Circular dependency** — `PatientService` ↔ `BillingService` uses `@Lazy` workaround | 🟡 Major |
| 7 | **No family wallet** — Wallet only supports `CENTER` entity type, no `FAMILY` wallets | 🟡 Major |
| 8 | **HR module incomplete** — Attendance, leave, payroll entities exist but logic is minimal | 🟡 Major |
| 9 | **No QR code generation** — Health card system requires QR codes | 🟡 Major |
| 10 | **Doctor scheduling incomplete** — Slots and appointment booking not fully implemented | 🟡 Major |

#### Frontend Issues
| # | Issue | Severity |
|---|-------|----------|
| 1 | **Generic UI components** — `ApiFormCard` and `QueryTableCard` are JSON-dump forms, not user-friendly | 🔴 Critical |
| 2 | **No role-based navigation** — All 14 nav items shown to every user regardless of role | 🔴 Critical |
| 3 | **Manual ID entry** — Users must type raw IDs (centerId, patientId) instead of dropdowns/search | 🔴 Critical |
| 4 | **Bug: `endpoints.delete`** — Called in UsersPage but method is `endpoints.del` | 🔴 Bug |
| 5 | **Bug: `onSuccess` in useQuery** — React Query v5 removed `onSuccess` from `useQuery` options | 🔴 Bug |
| 6 | **No mobile sidebar** — Sidebar toggle exists in `uiStore` but sidebar doesn't respond | 🟡 Major |
| 7 | **Plain design** — White/blue only, no premium healthcare aesthetic | 🟡 Major |
| 8 | **No loading states** — Missing skeletons, spinners, and empty states | 🟡 Major |
| 9 | **No toast notifications** — Mutations silently succeed/fail | 🟡 Major |
| 10 | **No data validation** — Forms lack client-side validation | 🟡 Major |

